C. A. Blakeley, Appellant, v. Jackie Ann Fair, by Her Husband and Next Friend S. D. Fair, Appellee. Decision Filed January 8, 1923.

Petition for Rehearing Denied.

An Appeal from the Circuit Court for Osceola County; C. O. Andrews, Judge. Dickinson <& Dickinson, for Appellant; Johnson é Garrett, for Appellee. Per Curiam.

This cause .having heretofore been submitted to the court upon the transcript of the record of the decree herein, and briefs and argument of counsel for the respective parties, and the record having been seen and inspected, and the court being now advised of its judgment to be given in the premises, it seems to the court that there is no error in the said decree; it is, therefore, com sidered, ordered and adjudged by the court that the said decree of the Circuit Court be, and the same is hereby affirmed.

All concur.
